QX|B4,2NT to Show Limit Raise|cs|6|at|
^-{    2NT to Show Limit Raise    }
^-|CS||cp|8|AT|

^B@2^*BHoward: ^*N|cp||at|Now let me discuss a couple of advanced conventions. One is the use of 2N to show a limit raise. If you play that, then both 2N and a cue bid show a limit raise—of course then you give up 2N as a natural bid. According to this style, then the cheaper of 2N and the cue shows 3-card limit raise and the higher shows 4-cards. It would be better understood if we show you a few examples.|
PG| ***** 31 ***** |


